[l] Dieses Op-Ed argumentiert, dass man Kinder streiten lassen muss. Kreativitaet wird gehemmt von "Group-Think" und gefoerdert von Kritik und Argumenten.The skill to get hot without getting mad — to have a good argument that doesn’t become personal — is critical in life. But it’s one that few parents teach to their children. We want to give kids a stable home, so we stop siblings from quarreling and we have our own arguments behind closed doors. Yet if kids never get exposed to disagreement, we’ll end up limiting their creativity.
